Ansible Cofiguration
**************************************
Step 1: Clone three machines and set the hostname
      
  command : hostamectl set-hostname [name]     

  machine1 : Is a ansible controller 
     
    hostnamectl set-hostname ansible-controller
     exec bash

  machine2 : Is a ansible-target(or)node machine
    
    hostnamectl set-hostname ansi-node1
    exec bash

  machine3 : It is also another target machine  

   hostnamectl set-hostname ansi-node2
   exec bash

Step 2: update machines

 command : yum update -y

Step 3:Host configuration

 command: vim /etc/hosts

 inside the hosts file modify with target machines name and ip address

 example :
   192.168.106.167  ansi-node1
   192.168.106.168  ansi-node2

   save and exit [:wq]

Step 4: Genrate ssh key for all target machines using this way

  commands: cd /opt
  create one ssh file
 
   vim ssh-key :open and enter into the file inset below command

    ssh-key 
    ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub 192.168.106.166
    ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub ansible-controller
    ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub 192.168.106.167
    ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub ansi-node1
    ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub 192.168.106.168
    ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub ansi-node2

    save and exit[:wq]

Step 5: Give the file permission 
       
    command: chmod u+x ssh-key       
    
    then apply these command ./ssh-key
     
    by assigh  ssh key for each target asking permmisions type [yes] and asking password for each target machine give to root password

Step 6: Install the epel repository for Provides additional packages required for Ansible
   command : yum install epel-release -y

Step 7: Install ansible
   command : yum install ansible -y

Step 8: After installing the ansible goto the ansible directory
  
   command : cd /etc/ansible

Step 9: Modify the hosts file and add the groups

  example : [dbserver]
            192.168.106.167
            ansi-node1

            [testserver]
             192.168.106.168
             ansi-node2

  Here, dbserver and testserver is the groups,by naming the groups without intendation           
  
  complete the adding groups 

  save and exit[:wq]

 Step 10: Check the ping all target

 command: ansible -m ping all

 it gives the message "sucess" to assigned groups

 Step 11: Check the ping for particular group

   command: ansible -m ping group-name

   example: ansible -m ping dbserver

